3.speaker: POLAR BEAR
3.character: 新メニューのホットケーキ　味見してみて
3.definition: These pancakes are a new menu item. Try them out.

4.speaker: PANDA
4.definition: There's no bamboo grass in it.

6.speaker: PANDA
6.character: なんか　しょっぱい

7.speaker: POLAR BEAR
7.definition: I tried putting salmon in it.

8.speaker: POLAR BEAR
8.character: 笹子さんも食べてみてよ
8.definition: You should try it, too, Miss Sasako.

10.speaker: SASAKO
10.character: やっぱり　しょっぱいです

11.speaker: PANDA
11.character: あれ？ ペンギンさんいつからいたの？
11.definition: Oh, when did you get here, Mr. Penguin?

12.speaker: PENGUIN
12.definition: I've been here the whole time!

13.speaker: POLAR BEAR
13.character: ちゃんと気づいてたよ
13.definition: I noticed, but I wasn't sure if I should talk to you.

15.speaker: POLAR BEAR
15.character: シャケ入りホットケーキ　食べる？
15.definition: Would you like some salmon pancakes?

16.speaker: PENGUIN
16.character: 僕は今食欲なんかないの
16.definition: I don't feel like eating right now.

23.speaker: PENGUIN
23.definition: That would be a portable charcoal stove {\i1}(shichirin){\i0}.

26.speaker: PENGUIN
26.character: だから　僕は　失恋して ツッコむ気力もないの！
26.definition: My heart is broken, so I don't have the energy to retort!

27.speaker: POLAR BEAR
27.character: ツッコんでるじゃない

28.speaker: PANDA
28.character: 失恋って　ペン子さん？
28.definition: Did Miss Penko break your heart?

30.speaker: SASAKO
30.character: あ…　あの… なんて言ったらいいか…
30.definition: Um, I don't know what to say.

31.speaker: PENGUIN
31.character: 何も言わないで　ほっておいてよ
31.definition: Don't say anything. Just leave me alone.

32.speaker: POLAR BEAR
32.character: パンダくん駅前のベーグル屋さんおいしいらしいよ
32.definition: I hear that the bagel shop in front of the station is pretty good, Panda. Really?

34.speaker: SASAKO
34.character: 聞いてほしいんですか？

35.speaker: PENGUIN
35.definition: Of course! You'll feel better if you talk.

37.speaker: PENGUIN
37.character: って…　僕は 犯人じゃないから！
37.definition: Hey! I'm not a criminal! So, what happened?

40.speaker: PENGUIN
40.definition: Miss Penko was on a date. W-With who?

41.speaker: PENGUIN
41.character: それがなんと驚いたことに…

42.speaker: PENGUIN
42.character: 絶対に　ありえない相手で…
42.definition: It's someone you'd never expect... Yes?

43.speaker: PENGUIN
43.definition: I still can't believe it... Who was it?

44.speaker: PENGUIN
44.character: まさかと思うくらいの…

45.speaker: POLAR BEAR
45.character: いいから　早く吐け
45.definition: Hurry up and spit it out!

46.speaker: PENGUIN
46.character: って…　僕　犯人じゃないから！
46.definition: I told you, I'm not a criminal!

47.speaker: PENGUIN
47.character: さっき　公園で 目撃しちゃったんだ
47.definition: I saw them earlier at the park. Oh!

48.speaker: PENGUIN
48.definition: Miss Penko! What a chance encounter to see her here.

49.speaker: PENGUIN
49.character: 運命　感じちゃうな！

50.speaker: PENGUIN
50.character: やぁ！　偶然ですねペン…
50.definition: Well, this is unexpected Miss— Sorry... to... keep... you... waiting. Well, let's go. Really? Mr. Tortoise? Wow, really?

52.speaker: PENGUIN
52.character: そう…　ペン子さんと待ち合わせて デートしてたんだ
52.definition: That's right. They met up and went for a date.

53.speaker: PENKO
53.character: ステキなカフェですね

54.speaker: TORTOISE
54.character: 僕…　ここに 甲羅干しに来るんです～

60.speaker: PENGUIN
60.character: ２人で楽しそうにお茶飲んだり
60.definition: They were totally enjoying having tea at the café,

61.speaker: PENGUIN
61.character: あ～んってしたり ボートに乗ってたんだよ！
61.definition: and she was feeding him, and they were on a boat together!

62.speaker: POLAR BEAR
62.character: それ　どこで聞いてたの？
62.definition: Where were you hearing all of this?

64.speaker: POLAR BEAR
64.character: なんだか涙ぐましいね

65.speaker: PANDA
65.character: でも　それだけじゃ
65.definition: But I don't think any of those things mean they're going out.

66.speaker: PENGUIN
66.character: それが　決定的なことに…
66.definition: But then something happened to make it official...

67.speaker: PENKO
67.character: 私…　大好きなんですよね

69.speaker: PENGUIN
69.character: 知らなかった…　ペン子さん カメが大好きだったなんて…
69.definition: I had no idea that Miss Penko liked turtles.

70.speaker: PENGUIN
70.character: カメのどこがいいんだろう？

71.speaker: PENGUIN
71.character: ねぇどこがいいんだと思う？
71.definition: I'm asking you, what's so good about them?

73.speaker: SASAKO
73.character: こ…　甲羅があるとこですかね？
73.definition: M-Maybe because they have a shell?

74.speaker: POLAR BEAR
74.character: 首とか手足が引っ込むところも キュートかも
74.definition: The fact that their head and legs scrunch in might be cute. It's amazing that they live for a thousand years.

75.speaker: PENGUIN
75.character: ペ…　ペンギンにだって いいとこあるでしょ？

77.speaker: PENGUIN
77.character: 負けてる…　完璧に負けてるよ

78.speaker: PENGUIN
78.character: 僕はどうして ペンギンに生まれたんだろう
78.definition: Why was I born a penguin?

79.speaker: PENGUIN
79.character: お母さん！　どうして　僕を カメに生んでくれなかったの！？
79.definition: Mom, why didn't you give birth to me as a turtle?

80.speaker: PANDA
80.character: ペンギンさん　あのね

81.speaker: PANDA
81.character: ペンギンからカメは生まれないんだよ
81.definition: penguins don't give birth to turtles.

83.speaker: PENGUIN
83.character: あ～あ… こんなことなら思い切って
83.definition: Aw man, if I knew this was going to happen...

84.speaker: PENGUIN
84.character: ペン子さんを ドライブに誘っとくんだった
84.definition: I should have just asked Miss Penko out for a drive.

85.speaker: SASAKO
85.character: い…　今からでも遅くないですよ
85.definition: I-I don't think it's too late. Huh?

86.speaker: POLAR BEAR
86.character: せっかく免許も取ったんだし…
86.definition: You did just get your license...

88.speaker: PANDA
88.character: ペン子さんカメ好きなら
88.definition: But if Miss Penko likes turtles, she might not like fast things.

89.speaker: PENGUIN
89.character: ゆっくりじゃないとダメなのか～！
89.definition: So it has to be slow?!

91.speaker: PENGUIN
91.character: もう　きっぱり ペン子さんのことは諦めよう
91.definition: I'm going to give up on Miss Penko completely.

92.speaker: SASAKO
92.definition: That might be for the better. Yup. You'll find another nice girl.

93.speaker: PENGUIN
93.character: そうだよね　いつまでも 引きずってちゃダメだよね
93.definition: You're right, I've got to move on. Yup.

95.speaker: PENGUIN
95.character: やっぱ　諦めちゃダメでしょ！
95.definition: I shouldn't give up that easily!

97.speaker: SASAKO
97.character: でも　ペン子さんには　ゾウガメさんが…
97.definition: But Miss Penko has Mr. Tortoise.

98.speaker: PENGUIN
98.character: ペンギンがゾウガメなんかに 負けてたまるか～っ！
98.definition: There's no way I'm going to lose to a tortoise!

99.speaker: POLAR BEAR
99.character: あっ　ゾウガメさん

102.speaker: PANDA
102.character: ペン子さんの彼氏　来た

103.speaker: SASAKO
103.character: ダメだよ　そんなこと言っちゃ

104.speaker: PANDA
104.definition: Are you going to duel now?

106.speaker: PANDA
106.character: えっと　こういうのたしか…
106.definition: Um, I think they call this shabadaba.

107.speaker: SASAKO
107.definition: You mean a clash of titans {\i1}(shuraba){\i0}.

108.speaker: PENGUIN
108.definition: Hey, shut up for a second!

109.speaker: PENGUIN
109.character: とにかく　ペン子さんと どういうおつきあいなのか
109.definition: Anyways, I have to find out what he's doing with

110.definition: Miss Penko once and for all.

114.speaker: PANDA
114.character: ペンギンさん　はっきりさせるんじゃ なかったの？
114.definition: Weren't you going to find out what he's doing, Mr. Penguin?

117.speaker: PENGUIN
117.character: あ…　いや…　あのさ！ この間さ　公園で…
117.definition: Um, well... I-I was wondering, at the park the other day... I ate a really delicious sardine.

120.speaker: PENGUIN
120.definition: I know that! There's a certain order in conversations!

121.speaker: PENGUIN
121.character: そういえば　あの公園でさ
121.definition: Oh yeah, at the park, you were with a girl penguin, right?

122.speaker: PENGUIN
122.character: あの公園　気持いいよね

123.speaker: POLAR BEAR
123.character: で　ゾウガメさんとペン子さんは どういう関係？
123.definition: So, what's the relationship between you and Miss Penko, Mr. Tortoise?

124.speaker: PENGUIN
124.character: あからさまに聞かないでよ！
124.definition: Don't be so blunt about it!

125.speaker: SASAKO
125.character: それで　ゾウガメさんは どうして一緒に？
125.definition: So why were you two together? You, too, Miss Sasako?!

126.speaker: PANDA
126.character: なんで　公園に一緒にいたの？
126.definition: Why were you two together at the park?

127.speaker: TORTOISE
127.definition: I was... invited... Miss Penko invited you?

130.speaker: PENGUIN
130.character: ゾウガメさん　ペン子さんとお幸せに！ うわ～ん！
130.definition: May you two live happily together!

132.speaker: PENGUIN
132.definition: Wait a second. If Miss Penko likes turtles so much...

135.speaker: POLAR BEAR
135.character: 何やってるの　ペンギンさん
135.definition: What are you doing, Mr. Penguin? Where did you get that shell?

137.speaker: PENGUIN
137.character: ペン子さんはカメが大好き

138.speaker: POLAR BEAR
138.character: ああ　ペン子さんはね
138.definition: Oh, about that... What Miss Penko really likes are cameras, not turtles (kame). Huh?

139.speaker: POLAR BEAR
139.character: 最近　カメラが趣味らしいよ
139.definition: Apparently she's really into cameras as of late.

140.speaker: SASAKO
140.character: ゾウガメさんも同じ趣味みたいで
140.definition: Mr. Tortoise apparently has the same hobby.

141.speaker: PANDA
141.character: 大好きなのはね　カメじゃなくてカメラだよ
141.definition: What she really likes are cameras, not turtles.
